# Blazor Web Client Guidelines

## Purpose
This project contains the Blazor web client application. It provides the user interface for the JAIMES AF game system.

## Key Principles
- **Component-based UI**: Use Razor components for UI elements
- **Interactive Components**: Pages with interactive components must include `@rendermode InteractiveAuto` directive
- **API Communication**: Use HttpClient or API client services to communicate with the backend
- **State Management**: Use Blazor's built-in features (CascadingParameters, EventCallbacks) for state

## Component Structure
- Pages are in `Components/Pages/` folder
- Shared components can be in `Components/` or `Components/Shared/`
- Helper classes (e.g., API clients) are at the project root
- Use code-behind files (`.razor.cs`) for complex logic

## Rendering Modes
- Use `@rendermode InteractiveAuto` for pages that need interactivity
- This enables server-side rendering with automatic WebAssembly fallback
- Static pages don't need render mode directives

## API Integration
- Create API client services for backend communication
- Use dependency injection to inject HttpClient or API clients
- Handle errors gracefully and provide user feedback
- Use async/await for all API calls

## Common Patterns
```razor
@page "/example"
@rendermode InteractiveAuto
@inject IExampleApiClient ApiClient

<PageTitle>Example</PageTitle>

<h1>Example Page</h1>

@if (loading)
{
    <p>Loading...</p>
}
else if (error != null)
{
    <p class="text-danger">@error</p>
}
else
{
    @foreach (var item in items)
    {
        <p>@item.Name</p>
    }
}

@code {
    private bool loading = true;
    private string? error;
    private ExampleItem[] items = Array.Empty<ExampleItem>();

    protected override async Task OnInitializedAsync()
    {
        try
        {
            items = await ApiClient.GetItemsAsync();
        }
        catch (Exception ex)
        {
            error = ex.Message;
        }
        finally
        {
            loading = false;
        }
    }
}
```

## Styling
- Use CSS files alongside components when needed
- Follow existing styling patterns
- Use CSS isolation (`.razor.css`) for component-specific styles

## Testing
- Web component tests are in `JAIMES AF.Tests/` if applicable
- Test API client services and helper classes
- Use browser automation tools for UI testing if needed

